race.comment: LONDON'S IMAGE (3) was very strong first-up in the Crawford and that form has been franked since. Been given time to get over the first-up effort and Fiore remains in the saddle. Expecting her to roll forward from the barrier and with improvement on the cards, she'll be tough to run down. TOROPA (5) wasn't far away first-up over 1000m and she'll be much better for that run. She's a second-up winner in the past and up to 1200m now is a big tick. Came into this without a trial, so she'll have plenty of improvement to come and she looks the main danger. YORGA PRIDE (12) is a lightly raced mare who has hinted she's up to this grade. Her latest run was only fair in Bm66+ grade, but she ticks plenty of boxes today with Pike back on board from a good gate. Expecting a much better performance today. CHOLLIMA (7) was only 1.5L off the winner last start and the inside draw helps her chances. TWAIN'S ANGEL (1) is third-up now and can go close with that form tying in through the Crawford.
